generation/baseline/coder_contract.md:585:`runOneSpin` starts by selecting `BG1_Reels` or `BG2_Reels` from `probTable.ReelsetWeights`, then builds a `[4x6]` base window. Base additional COR is optionally injected using `corTrigger`, `numCorWeight`, and `baseCORValueWeights`, while preserving the rule that added COR cannot overwrite `COLLECT`, `WILD`, or `SCAT`.
generation/baseline/coder_contract.md:589:If three or more base `SCAT` symbols appear, the caller-provided feature choice determines whether to run Free Spins (`FreeGameFeature_1`) or Blitz Spins (`FreeGameFeature_2`). Free Spins use `FG1_Reels`, apply all visible WILD multipliers to ways wins, and support retriggers. Blitz Spins generate COR/COLLECT-only windows, guarantee at least one COLLECT and one COR, assign one Good-table COR value per spin and Bad-table values to all other CORs, then resolve Collect.
